Introduction

ARTMS, also known as Artemis Strategy, is a girl group project launched by MODHAUS in April 2023. It is formed by former LOONA members: Heejin, Haseul, Kim Lip, Jinsoul, and Choerry.

The name “ARTMS” draws inspiration from the Greek goddess “Artemis,” who is closely associated with the moon. Consequently, it connects with other entities named after this celestial figure. The group’s concept is to pay homage to the LOONA universe through the moon-like god, ARTMS. In their first project trailer, they depicted twelve months, each marked by a full moon representing HeeJin, Kim Lip, JinSoul, and Choerry. Their motto captures their mission: “We rise together, back to the moon and beyond.”

Their fandom name "OURII" is a combination of letters in each member's name: jinsOul, haseUl, choerRy, heejIn, and kIm lip. It also means "us" in Korean.

Through the ARTMS project, the trio ODD EYE CIRCLE returned with their new mini album Version Up in July 2023. Since ODD EYE CIRCLE's re-debut, 2 more members have been added, Haseul and Heejin, also former members of LOONA. ARTMS released 'The Carol 3.0' on December 1st, 2023 with all 5 members.

They made their debut on May 31, 2024, with their first album Dall. Shortly after the release, they embarked on their first world tour 'Moonshot'.
